==English==

===Etymology 1===
{{etyl|enm}} ''hondfast'', past participle of ''[[hondfesten]] 'to betroth', from Old Norse [[handfesta]] 'to strike a bargain, pledge', itself from [[hönd]] 'hand' + ''[[festa]] 'to fasten, fix, affirm' (compare see [[past-]] in Indo-European roots).

====Noun====
'''handfast'''

# {{obsolete}} A [[hold]], grasp; [[custody]], power of confining or keeping.
# {{obsolete}} A [[contract]], agreement, covenant ; specifically [[betrothal]], [[espousal]].

